Definition.WordDefinition: Cayman \Cay"man\ (k[=a]"man), n. [From the language of Guiana: cf. Sp. caiman.] (Zo["o]l.) The south America alligator. See {Alligator}. [Sometimes written {caiman}.] [1913 Webster] ||
cayman n : an alligator-like reptile of Central America and South America having a more heavily armored belly [syn: {caiman}]
